WEBVTT

01:16.063 --> 01:16.896
Yeah...

01:17.896 --> 01:19.229
Come on, fall!

01:38.146 --> 01:40.062
They must really like you.

01:40.063 --> 01:41.687
Sending you expensive eel.

01:41.688 --> 01:43.105
It's not that they like me.

01:43.688 --> 01:45.604
They're going to work me even harder.

01:45.938 --> 01:47.271
Those Americans too

01:47.604 --> 01:50.521
must know that eels
make men perform better.

01:51.813 --> 01:54.646
They even sent it on your birthday.

01:57.688 --> 01:58.813
The kids will hear!

01:59.813 --> 02:03.312
I need eel! Eel!

02:03.521 --> 02:05.021
Come and eat!

02:05.646 --> 02:09.438
Dad sweated in the heat grilling these.

02:09.730 --> 02:10.729
I'll go.

02:17.813 --> 02:18.729
A snake?

02:19.771 --> 02:21.228
Snakes don't taste this good!

02:21.229 --> 02:24.146
Dad's company sent it,
for doing a good job.

02:24.438 --> 02:25.813
It's not even a holiday.

02:26.730 --> 02:28.604
Couldn't they give us beef?

02:29.855 --> 02:30.855
Ri-one.

02:31.438 --> 02:32.396
Dinner.

02:35.271 --> 02:37.855
Come on. Let's eat.

02:39.479 --> 02:41.146
Let the cello take a nap.

02:45.354 --> 02:46.521
What's this?

02:56.062 --> 02:58.855
Honey!

03:01.730 --> 03:03.938
Must've been expensive!

03:05.021 --> 03:08.104
Well, I can afford decent dance shoes.

03:08.688 --> 03:11.271
- Aren't Mom's shoes pretty?
- Eat up.

03:14.312 --> 03:16.187
I'll be able to dance so well in these.

03:19.563 --> 03:22.271
They say not to gift shoes to your lover.

03:22.688 --> 03:23.271
Why?

03:23.438 --> 03:24.146
Why?

03:24.438 --> 03:26.563
‘Cause they might run away in them.

03:27.646 --> 03:30.521
Seems your dad is confident.

03:32.146 --> 03:33.104
Come on.

03:34.187 --> 03:36.104
We need to practice when we can.

03:37.896 --> 03:39.479
Ready, start!

03:39.896 --> 03:41.645
One two three,

03:41.646 --> 03:45.729
two two three, three two three...

04:10.896 --> 04:13.478
Thanks for your hard work
and years of dedication to Solar Paper.

04:13.479 --> 04:15.563
Damned paper...

04:16.604 --> 04:18.477
Honey, come here.

04:18.478 --> 04:19.438
Why?

04:21.354 --> 04:21.979
Come on.

04:23.729 --> 04:25.146
Come on, Ri-one.

04:27.771 --> 04:33.896
Ri-two Si-two

04:37.771 --> 04:39.187
Just three minutes more.

04:40.062 --> 04:41.396
One minute...

04:49.938 --> 04:51.563
Know what I'm feeling now?

04:55.312 --> 04:56.813
I've got it all.

05:33.062 --> 05:37.688
You people bought Solar Paper,
where I devoted 25 years of my life.

05:38.438 --> 05:40.228
But as soon as you take over, you say

05:40.229 --> 05:42.688
you'll cut 20% of the production line?

05:43.354 --> 05:45.563
And you ask for a list
of names to fire?

05:46.479 --> 05:49.354
Names of veterans
who taught me their craft?

05:50.312 --> 05:52.895
Names of young men
who came of age in this factory?

05:54.146 --> 05:56.855
Innocent workers who lovingly
cared for these machines,

05:57.104 --> 06:00.479
you want me to point a gun at their heads?

06:01.604 --> 06:02.895
I can't do it.

06:04.146 --> 06:06.728
Guns are meant to be aimed
at one's enemies!

06:06.729 --> 06:07.603
Stop! Think! Act!

06:07.604 --> 06:10.563
I cannot give you that list.

06:13.062 --> 06:15.104
You Americans say

06:15.354 --> 06:16.979
to be fired is to be ‘axed'?

06:17.813 --> 06:19.646
Know what we say in Korea?

06:19.813 --> 06:21.187
Off with your head!

06:21.563 --> 06:23.396
So being fired

06:24.646 --> 06:28.271
is having your head chopped
clear off with an ax!

06:33.895 --> 06:34.978
Job for life, old shoes

06:34.979 --> 06:37.937
“If you don't start a union,
we guarantee a job for life.”

06:38.312 --> 06:42.854
That beautiful tradition...
tossed out like old shoes!

06:43.146 --> 06:45.103
To you Americans...!

06:45.104 --> 06:46.271
Damn, my throat...

06:46.854 --> 06:48.646
I said to do this in the warehouse.

06:49.271 --> 06:51.146
All because you wanted to smoke.

06:52.062 --> 06:52.978
Quit, dammit!

06:52.979 --> 06:55.145
You put so much work into this.

06:55.146 --> 06:57.061
He could've said, forget it.

06:57.062 --> 07:00.646
- But he acts like it's his job at stake.
- It is!

07:00.854 --> 07:03.270
If you guys are fired,
who will I work with?

07:03.271 --> 07:04.979
Real sense of humanity.

07:05.521 --> 07:06.521
Damn.

07:09.187 --> 07:10.187
Stop!

07:18.187 --> 07:19.146
Hello, sir.

07:29.854 --> 07:31.395
Off with your head!

07:31.396 --> 07:33.687
- So to be fired...
- Give back the helmet!

07:33.688 --> 07:35.646
...is to chop your head clear off!

07:36.020 --> 07:36.812
Wait!

07:38.312 --> 07:40.229
What'll he do with that helmet?

07:47.563 --> 07:48.229
They didn't...

07:49.271 --> 07:50.521
give you the eel, did they?

07:55.354 --> 07:56.604
No way, right?

08:04.438 --> 08:05.312
Honey.

08:06.937 --> 08:07.688
What?

08:08.354 --> 08:09.979
You said you'd say something.

08:12.312 --> 08:13.271
I forgot.

08:13.521 --> 08:15.103
Aren't you going to work?

08:15.104 --> 08:16.229
Right, right.

08:16.604 --> 08:17.438
That's right.

08:19.354 --> 08:20.937
Si-two Ri-two, house!

08:21.854 --> 08:23.187
Study hard.

08:25.646 --> 08:27.769
- Ri-one, let's go.
- Ri-one!

08:27.770 --> 08:30.020
Have a good day.

08:35.604 --> 08:36.146
Good luck!

08:38.979 --> 08:41.312
I slaved for 25 years!

08:49.604 --> 08:50.688
Deep breaths.

09:07.354 --> 09:08.979
- I am...
- I am...

09:09.479 --> 09:10.604
A good person.

09:10.770 --> 09:12.145
A good person.

09:12.146 --> 09:13.062
Man-su!

09:13.770 --> 09:14.520
...person.

09:14.521 --> 09:16.271
- Losing my job...
- Losing my job...

09:16.770 --> 09:19.104
- Losing my job!
- Losing my job...

09:19.812 --> 09:23.062
is not my choice!

09:26.354 --> 09:29.228
- My loving family...
- My loving family...

09:29.229 --> 09:31.020
My loving family...

09:31.895 --> 09:35.312
will support me fully
as I seek new opportunities.

09:35.770 --> 09:39.770
...as I seek new opportunities.

09:40.438 --> 09:44.479
My loving family will support me fully

09:44.770 --> 09:46.728
as I seek new opportunities.

09:52.979 --> 09:54.271
Honey.

09:55.229 --> 09:56.727
Can you put in earphones?

09:56.728 --> 09:57.979
Just a sec.

09:59.479 --> 10:01.062
Hired in 3 months

10:05.104 --> 10:08.604
So you must've had
sleepless nights?

10:12.479 --> 10:13.645
Are you crying?

10:16.312 --> 10:21.020
Where's that brave bachelor
who proposed to a single mom?

10:21.812 --> 10:25.854
I made a new start, you can too.

10:27.187 --> 10:28.769
Sure you can!

10:28.770 --> 10:32.145
Take all your hopes and dreams,

10:32.146 --> 10:35.312
and recite your own incantation.

10:36.354 --> 10:37.146
Ready?

10:37.354 --> 10:38.645
Go!

10:41.479 --> 10:42.395
A new start...

10:42.396 --> 10:44.146
A new start... A new start...

10:44.645 --> 10:45.603
A new start.

10:45.937 --> 10:46.854
A new start.

10:47.729 --> 10:49.062
I'm head of a family.

10:50.563 --> 10:51.770
I'll be born again.

10:53.229 --> 10:56.687
To put food in my family's mouths...

10:57.521 --> 10:59.020
there's nothing I won't do.

11:01.438 --> 11:02.770
In three months,

11:04.812 --> 11:06.312
I'll get hired again!

11:10.312 --> 11:11.812
I feel great!

11:14.770 --> 11:17.478
3 Months Later

11:17.479 --> 11:20.520
13 Months Later

11:20.521 --> 11:22.686
Hi Namgu, I know.

11:22.687 --> 11:23.769
Today at 5 o'clock.

11:23.770 --> 11:25.937
My boss is really curious about you.

11:26.479 --> 11:30.187
Sorry to ask so suddenly,
but can you come at noon?

11:30.438 --> 11:31.979
Listen, I'm...

11:33.020 --> 11:35.020
at the retail store, with my wife.

11:36.396 --> 11:40.602
The boss suddenly booked
a 5pm flight back to China.

11:40.603 --> 11:41.270
Too much to ask?

11:41.271 --> 11:42.937
No no, hold on.

11:43.229 --> 11:43.895
Wait.

11:44.229 --> 11:46.978
I'll plead with my wife.

11:46.979 --> 11:49.854
That's right. Come over now.

11:50.396 --> 11:54.520
But there's a question he always asks.
“What's your weak point?”

11:54.895 --> 11:55.769
Weak point?

11:55.770 --> 12:00.437
It's a crucial-utely sensitive issue, okay?

12:00.438 --> 12:01.812
Okay, thanks!

12:23.895 --> 12:24.936
Weak point?

12:24.937 --> 12:28.019
Sorry, I know it's absolutely
impossible to answer.

12:28.020 --> 12:29.769
What's my weak point?

12:29.770 --> 12:33.978
What do you think?
You love plants too much.

12:33.979 --> 12:35.438
You're a vegetable.

12:36.312 --> 12:38.562
Last night you called me an animal.

12:41.062 --> 12:43.396
Namgu gave me this awesome tip.

12:44.770 --> 12:46.561
Mortgage Default Warning

12:46.562 --> 12:48.979
If only I can explain
my weak point well.

12:49.312 --> 12:51.895
It's a crucial-utely sensitive issue.

12:53.271 --> 12:57.769
If you're hired, you'll work
under your former subordinate Namgu.

12:57.770 --> 12:59.603
Tell us how you feel about that.

13:00.062 --> 13:01.936
I was a manager, true,

13:01.937 --> 13:06.020
but I've always considered
myself to be blue collar.

13:08.603 --> 13:10.311
So, in that respect...

13:10.312 --> 13:13.770
I don't think you understood the question.

13:15.562 --> 13:16.561
Namgu—

13:16.562 --> 13:19.437
No, of course I understand, my point is...

13:20.229 --> 13:24.104
Namgu came to Papyrus first,
so you'll learn from him, right?

13:24.312 --> 13:25.312
Of course!

13:26.271 --> 13:27.854
I am always learning.

13:28.312 --> 13:32.020
I got hired as soon as
I graduated from high school.

13:32.687 --> 13:37.228
But even while working,
I earned a chemistry degree.

13:37.229 --> 13:40.271
Of course, that was at
a distance university.

13:43.645 --> 13:48.271
Of course after that too,
I kept... learning.

13:48.562 --> 13:51.520
And of course, safety management.

13:52.478 --> 13:59.811
When I received the 2019
‘Pulp Man of the Year', it was that aspect

13:59.812 --> 14:02.146
that they singled out in my record.

14:02.812 --> 14:05.561
And that same year,

14:05.562 --> 14:08.271
I finally bought my own home.

14:09.062 --> 14:12.062
The very house I was born in.

14:12.395 --> 14:13.645
Of course...

14:14.354 --> 14:16.895
I'm saying “of course” too much, aren't I?

14:19.271 --> 14:22.770
It's not so much because I'm nervous,

14:23.395 --> 14:27.478
but... self-confidence? Assurance?
That's what it is.

14:28.020 --> 14:29.645
Of course!

14:34.062 --> 14:37.979
If you don't mind, could you
tell me about your weak point?

14:42.146 --> 14:43.187
No.

14:49.603 --> 14:54.353
...is the one thing I can't say,
that's my biggest weak point!

14:59.770 --> 15:01.645
Have you looked into Moon Paper?

15:01.895 --> 15:02.895
Moon?

15:03.562 --> 15:08.645
They say Moon Paper has cracked
the Japanese market, look into it.

15:09.020 --> 15:12.146
Pacific Paper is restructuring
this winter, too.

15:12.395 --> 15:13.020
Really?

15:14.020 --> 15:15.104
Go to a dentist, will you?

15:16.437 --> 15:17.603
Just go, okay?

15:18.812 --> 15:21.145
If you get hired,
you'll be too busy to go.

15:21.146 --> 15:22.561
No, I'm fine.

15:22.562 --> 15:25.311
There's that pigheadedness of yours!

15:26.062 --> 15:29.687
Anyway, get hired
before winter, okay?

15:30.062 --> 15:31.895
The company will call you soon.

15:33.062 --> 15:34.020
Thanks.

15:35.478 --> 15:37.895
Don't forget, Moon Paper!

15:39.562 --> 15:41.979
I'm a man. I'm a good person.

15:43.478 --> 15:46.602
Founded by legendary paper man
Moon Changho,

15:46.603 --> 15:47.686
Choi Sun-chul, Line Manager at Moon Paper

15:47.687 --> 15:49.186
- Moon Paper is...
- Mr. Choi!

15:49.187 --> 15:50.019
Yes?

15:50.020 --> 15:53.894
We agreed to talk about how paper is made.

15:53.895 --> 15:54.644
That's what I'm—

15:54.645 --> 15:56.645
Leave the promotion
to the company channel.

15:57.603 --> 15:58.894
6 hours 17 minutes later...

15:58.895 --> 16:03.062
Many people think paper companies
mindlessly raze entire forests, right?

16:03.520 --> 16:04.645
That's not true.

16:46.187 --> 16:46.687
What?

16:50.603 --> 16:52.104
First, the good news.

16:52.311 --> 16:54.687
I got a part time job.

16:54.854 --> 16:56.978
Mom's going out to work now!

16:56.979 --> 16:59.437
You always blamed us
for killing your career.

16:59.812 --> 17:00.728
Congrats, Mom!

17:00.895 --> 17:01.937
Congrats, Mom!

17:02.104 --> 17:03.395
Thanks.

17:03.729 --> 17:05.728
Where? A dental clinic?

17:06.146 --> 17:09.519
- Dr. Oh Chin-ho.
- Dr. Ouch In-ho?

17:09.520 --> 17:10.979
No jokes allowed.

17:11.394 --> 17:15.227
I'd like us all to face the fact
we're in a crisis.

17:15.729 --> 17:19.060
Refrain from the listed activities
until Dad finds work.

17:19.061 --> 17:22.812
Except for Ri-one's lessons,
anything nonessential must go.

17:23.437 --> 17:24.019
For example...

17:24.020 --> 17:25.519
For example, meat in the soup?

17:25.520 --> 17:28.020
There is some, look harder.

17:30.645 --> 17:31.770
For example,

17:32.062 --> 17:33.186
my car.

17:34.311 --> 17:36.729
We'll trade your car
for something smaller.

17:39.104 --> 17:41.353
And our house.

17:47.020 --> 17:51.437
If we sell the house, we can pay off
our loans and rent an apartment.

17:53.812 --> 17:56.394
You said you'd find work in 3 months.

17:56.395 --> 18:00.894
So we kept living as usual,
dipping into your severance pay.

18:00.895 --> 18:03.353
Now that's run dry.

18:09.478 --> 18:11.478
House Foreclosure in 3 Months

18:12.311 --> 18:13.437
Honey.

18:15.020 --> 18:16.395
This house...

18:20.437 --> 18:22.979
I have so many childhood memories
in this home.

18:24.520 --> 18:28.937
After turning 9, I moved
every 10 months on average.

18:29.104 --> 18:31.104
I worked so hard to buy back this home.

18:32.353 --> 18:33.645
I mean, we did.

18:35.062 --> 18:36.269
With my own hands,

18:36.270 --> 18:38.894
I tore down the old barn,
built the greenhouse...

18:38.895 --> 18:40.228
and the swing.

18:40.979 --> 18:42.894
Every corner of this home...

18:42.895 --> 18:43.895
Honey.

18:45.603 --> 18:48.311
If we go bankrupt, they'll take it anyway.

18:49.728 --> 18:50.769
The piano,

18:50.770 --> 18:51.936
living room table,

18:51.937 --> 18:52.936
two chairs,

18:52.937 --> 18:53.519
TV,

18:53.520 --> 18:54.436
curtain,

18:54.437 --> 18:55.144
carpet...

18:55.145 --> 18:56.769
have all been put up for sale.

18:56.770 --> 18:57.727
My racket, too.

18:57.728 --> 18:59.185
No more tennis.

18:59.186 --> 19:00.687
Let's quit dance lessons, too.

19:00.937 --> 19:02.520
Your bonsai magazine.

19:02.937 --> 19:04.895
And I'm canceling Netflix.

19:09.311 --> 19:10.186
Hey!

19:11.103 --> 19:13.687
Before it's cancelled,
I should watch one more show.

19:17.603 --> 19:21.437
So comrades, now for the bad news.

19:21.854 --> 19:23.020
Something even worse?

19:23.186 --> 19:24.520
Something even worse?

19:28.937 --> 19:32.979
In these circumstances,
we can't afford to feed so many mouths.

19:35.061 --> 19:36.937
What do you mean, so many?

19:37.478 --> 19:39.353
- Don't go, Ri-two.
- Ri-one.

19:40.186 --> 19:41.269
Si-one.

19:41.270 --> 19:43.561
We'll see them soon, okay Ri-one?

19:43.562 --> 19:45.019
Come on.

19:45.020 --> 19:48.561
You can come visit them
at our house. Okay?

19:48.562 --> 19:51.812
Si-two Ri-two will be back.
As soon as Dad gets hired.

20:03.937 --> 20:06.060
That dog hair is brutal.

20:06.061 --> 20:07.520
I'm sorry, Dad.

20:09.729 --> 20:10.729
Have a safe drive.

20:12.979 --> 20:13.769
Let's go in.

20:13.770 --> 20:14.770
Come on.

20:16.395 --> 20:18.812
I'll bring them back soon, I will.

20:25.061 --> 20:26.394
Hello, ma'am!

20:26.395 --> 20:27.979
You're here early!

20:29.812 --> 20:32.311
The potential buyer is that dickhead?

20:34.812 --> 20:37.728
Not bad for a 50-year-old house.

20:37.729 --> 20:39.145
Look at the curtains.

20:39.770 --> 20:43.686
They fixed up this ruined house so well.

20:43.687 --> 20:45.352
It's been born again.

20:45.353 --> 20:48.270
- You know my townhouse near here?
- Yes.

20:48.437 --> 20:51.729
That land was originally
part of his dad's pig farm.

20:52.186 --> 20:54.603
Wow, if he still owned that land...

20:54.812 --> 20:58.437
If we tear down that greenhouse,
it'd make a great practice green.

21:01.186 --> 21:02.437
Disgusting pig.

21:03.103 --> 21:05.854
You're quite the handyman,
You Man-su.

21:10.937 --> 21:12.687
That's enough for today.

21:14.186 --> 21:15.686
The moms are besties.

21:15.687 --> 21:17.395
The kids are besties.

21:20.729 --> 21:22.478
Pulp Man of the Year!

21:23.937 --> 21:26.019
Your dad's gun is still looking good...

21:27.228 --> 21:29.061
Vietnam War Service Certificate

21:32.728 --> 21:34.520
Oh, look here!

21:34.812 --> 21:40.935
Imagine waking up and seeing
that sturdy red pine!

21:40.936 --> 21:42.019
It's a white pine.

21:43.019 --> 21:44.019
White pine...

21:44.186 --> 21:46.853
Look around.
I'll stop by the dry cleaners.

21:46.854 --> 21:48.769
Pick up my clothes for an interview.

21:48.770 --> 21:51.103
You're a Man! Su! Fight!

21:53.395 --> 21:54.978
Shall we see the kids' rooms?

21:56.770 --> 21:59.227
With just one kid,
we'll use that as a closet.

21:59.228 --> 22:01.186
I thought that too!

22:02.978 --> 22:04.228
Nice mattress.

22:06.270 --> 22:08.186
That's for sale too, buy it.

22:12.645 --> 22:14.145
Where will you move to?

22:15.186 --> 22:17.061
Need to sell the house first.

22:18.311 --> 22:19.728
Hope you don't go far.

22:21.978 --> 22:24.978
If we leave, Si-two Ri-two
won't be able to find us.

22:25.186 --> 22:26.228
Says who?

22:36.311 --> 22:37.562
We're not leaving.

22:38.728 --> 22:39.812
I promise.

22:40.645 --> 22:44.018
Si-one Ri-one Si-one Ri-one...

22:44.019 --> 22:45.978
Si-two Ri-two Si-two...

22:46.353 --> 22:47.520
Let me through!

22:47.854 --> 22:50.186
- I'm late for a meeting.
- Listen, please.

22:51.311 --> 22:53.729
My wife is doing part time work,

22:54.019 --> 22:56.644
we put our home up for sale,

22:56.645 --> 22:58.228
- cancelled Netflix...
- What?

22:59.645 --> 23:00.602
Sir?

23:00.603 --> 23:01.395
Choi Sun-chul!

23:01.770 --> 23:03.602
What's going on? Who's this?

23:03.603 --> 23:05.602
He was fired from Solar.

23:05.603 --> 23:06.853
Just a sec.

23:09.520 --> 23:10.311
Come out.

23:12.186 --> 23:13.395
I'm sorry.

23:13.729 --> 23:14.686
Going to the meeting?

23:14.687 --> 23:16.269
I wanted to talk to you.

23:16.270 --> 23:17.061
Sure, then.

23:24.145 --> 23:26.103
Let me look...

23:26.395 --> 23:28.311
God, you're strong.

23:32.687 --> 23:34.770
If you have any shame,

23:35.437 --> 23:38.353
don't do this in a place
where people shit and piss.

23:41.978 --> 23:43.103
Sir!

23:43.770 --> 23:47.018
I told you to come visit me!
We'll have a nice barbecue.

23:47.019 --> 23:49.019
All right, then.

24:00.562 --> 24:01.353
Oh my.

24:04.437 --> 24:05.645
Listen.

24:06.728 --> 24:11.520
On the hill opposite, there's a nice
whisky bar called Moon Shine.

24:12.103 --> 24:13.729
Have a drink on your way.

24:14.228 --> 24:17.810
I just moved here to Hoi Island.

24:17.811 --> 24:19.311
It's really gorgeous.

24:19.894 --> 24:23.894
Revealed for the first time ever!
Give a shout!

24:24.603 --> 24:28.769
Barbecue over my own wood fire
is out of this world!

24:29.729 --> 24:31.729
Die!

24:45.603 --> 24:48.269
For each drop of sweat, a drop of whisky!

24:48.270 --> 24:51.768
It's what I live for.

24:51.769 --> 24:54.853
Ms. Wife

24:54.978 --> 24:55.935
Hi honey.

24:55.936 --> 24:58.936
Listen, the cello teacher called...

24:59.645 --> 25:01.478
- Where are you?
- Huh?

25:03.478 --> 25:05.103
- Are you in a bar?
- No no.

25:05.894 --> 25:07.687
Well, it's true.

25:08.645 --> 25:09.727
It's true, but I'm not.

25:09.728 --> 25:10.728
Look.

25:12.603 --> 25:13.602
I'm by myself.

25:13.603 --> 25:14.645
Have you gone mad?

25:15.395 --> 25:17.478
- I'm drinking this, really.
- Whisky?

25:17.978 --> 25:19.270
This here.

25:20.478 --> 25:22.478
You went to a bar
to drink apple juice?

25:22.811 --> 25:25.603
Honey, you trust me?

25:28.311 --> 25:30.144
Of course.

25:30.145 --> 25:31.395
Why'd the cello teacher call?

25:31.687 --> 25:37.603
I can't teach Ri-one anymore.

25:39.019 --> 25:39.810
What?

25:39.811 --> 25:42.437
Ri-one's talent is too...

25:42.936 --> 25:44.103
outstanding?

25:49.853 --> 25:51.270
But ma'am,

25:52.686 --> 25:56.145
how can I believe you?

25:57.019 --> 26:00.936
She doesn't play for us.

26:01.645 --> 26:05.311
We've never heard anything
but a few notes.

26:05.728 --> 26:06.353
Right.

26:06.562 --> 26:12.603
Why do you think I'd give up
my lesson fee to another teacher?

26:12.936 --> 26:14.102
Another teacher?

26:14.103 --> 26:17.353
Ri-one needs to learn
from a music professor now.

26:18.978 --> 26:23.061
But you should know,
the fee is on a different level than mine.

26:26.936 --> 26:32.520
You said you wanted Ri-one
to be able to live independently.

26:36.686 --> 26:39.019
If so, this level of investment—

26:39.644 --> 26:41.853
I'll say two things.

26:42.686 --> 26:47.227
Many people think paper companies
mindlessly raze entire forests, right?

26:47.228 --> 26:48.685
That's not true.

26:48.686 --> 26:52.060
Trees for paper are grown separately, cut,

26:52.061 --> 26:55.728
planted again, grown and cut again.

26:56.520 --> 26:59.227
And that's not all. There's reuse.

26:59.228 --> 27:01.562
We collect waste paper, recycle it,

27:02.728 --> 27:06.228
- then collect it again and—
- What are you watching?

27:09.145 --> 27:11.894
The only company doing well
these days is Moon Paper.

27:12.145 --> 27:15.644
They cracked the Japanese market.
He's line manager of specialty paper.

27:16.686 --> 27:19.562
A perfect job for you.
You're good at Japanese, too.

27:21.270 --> 27:25.061
Korea's the most advanced country
in paper reuse.

27:27.186 --> 27:28.353
Unlimited reuse!

27:28.727 --> 27:30.228
Freaking unlimited reuse!

27:30.562 --> 27:32.562
Compared to my husband, he's nothing.

27:35.562 --> 27:37.395
Can't he get hit by lightning?

27:38.311 --> 27:41.145
Pointy umbrella in a thunderstorm...

27:56.019 --> 27:58.478
Choi Sun-chul

28:33.728 --> 28:36.061
Sure, it's fabulous!

28:37.769 --> 28:40.019
Try living there just one week.

28:43.019 --> 28:45.727
An apartment can't even compare!

28:49.936 --> 28:52.561
Come on, the ferry runs so often!

28:55.186 --> 28:56.437
I'm telling you.

28:57.061 --> 29:00.936
I know that, but it's so quiet there.

29:01.437 --> 29:03.395
Air's clean, it's fabulous.

29:05.270 --> 29:07.853
Even more fabulous at night...

29:20.978 --> 29:21.853
Right.

29:24.936 --> 29:26.769
No, there aren't any!

29:27.686 --> 29:31.894
If you're scared, we'll raise chickens.
They eat snakes.

29:33.145 --> 29:34.145
What?

29:34.686 --> 29:36.686
Listen, honey...

29:38.145 --> 29:40.686
For once, at least come for a barbecue!

29:41.894 --> 29:45.228
Pork! Who roasts snakes?

29:48.936 --> 29:51.145
No alcohol, of course.

30:29.477 --> 30:30.727
Weight lifting?

30:35.769 --> 30:37.270
Honey! Honey!

30:43.978 --> 30:46.269
Even if this guy disappears,

30:46.270 --> 30:48.436
it's not like I can take his place.

30:49.644 --> 30:50.602
Right?

30:52.061 --> 30:54.019
What's so great about that spot?

31:03.644 --> 31:06.186
The competition for the place
will be fierce.

31:06.769 --> 31:09.103
Actually, it is a pretty nice spot.

31:09.519 --> 31:11.561
Lots of sun, nice breeze.

31:12.145 --> 31:13.270
Right...

31:14.769 --> 31:17.353
How many other candidates will there be?

31:18.519 --> 31:19.727
Ten people?

31:23.644 --> 31:24.686
Five?

31:27.477 --> 31:29.352
Moon Paper

31:29.686 --> 31:30.727
Four?

31:37.644 --> 31:40.145
Sell me this.
How much do you want?

32:02.394 --> 32:03.935
This is Pulp Men.

32:03.936 --> 32:06.228
Is this the advertising division?

32:07.103 --> 32:07.936
Hey.

32:08.352 --> 32:11.186
At least give me
those pajamas to wash.

32:11.769 --> 32:13.769
And take a shower this century!

32:15.310 --> 32:17.477
And will you let our pear tree die?

32:17.644 --> 32:19.644
Bugs are swarming all over it.

32:20.686 --> 32:23.394
Hey! You want me dead, too?

32:39.310 --> 32:41.061
Too drunk to feel pain?

32:41.310 --> 32:44.268
You're practically paralyzed!

32:44.269 --> 32:47.061
It's because of all those bugs.

32:47.436 --> 32:50.103
So what I'm asking is...

32:50.811 --> 32:52.728
You're the bug!

32:53.769 --> 32:57.894
...please give me a drop of remedy.

33:00.145 --> 33:01.103
I'll be back late.

33:01.477 --> 33:03.394
I have a meeting after the audition!

33:17.310 --> 33:19.477
Paper is our life!

33:19.936 --> 33:24.644
A master's degree in paper
or chemical engineering is required.

33:25.061 --> 33:26.477
Japanese speakers preferred.

33:27.103 --> 33:29.852
We at Red Pepper Paper,

33:29.853 --> 33:33.935
together with European and Japanese firms

33:33.936 --> 33:37.686
are launching a three-company
joint venture in Korea.

33:38.894 --> 33:44.727
Our goal is to be the top boutique factory
in specialized security paper.

33:45.352 --> 33:48.935
We seek family, not cogs in a machine.

33:48.936 --> 33:52.268
Tell us about your hobbies,
personality and family.

33:52.269 --> 33:55.435
Give us a photo
as large and recent as possible.

33:55.436 --> 33:58.977
Send it to P.O. Box 76,
Gujong City Central Post Office.

33:58.978 --> 34:01.393
We firmly reject applications by internet.

34:01.394 --> 34:03.936
If we don't use paper, who will?

34:08.019 --> 34:10.309
My name is Gu Bummo.

34:10.811 --> 34:12.936
As a resolutely analogue person,

34:13.227 --> 34:16.726
I play music only on vinyl,
take photos only on film,

34:16.727 --> 34:18.810
and write letters only on paper.

34:20.519 --> 34:24.102
My bond to paper, as durable
as reinforced synthetic paper,

34:24.103 --> 34:26.936
began before I was even born.

34:27.769 --> 34:30.726
Encouraged by my uncle,
a first generation paper man,

34:30.727 --> 34:33.686
I enrolled in paper manufacturing
at Kangwon University.

34:35.185 --> 34:38.935
After serving in the Marines,
I joined Namsun Paper in 1999.

34:39.853 --> 34:43.560
In 2013, I oversaw
the reinforced paper line

34:43.561 --> 34:46.769
with most of our customers
coming from the defense industry.

34:47.560 --> 34:50.269
Winning Pulp Man of the Year in 2018...

34:51.685 --> 34:53.309
“To Red Pepper Paper HR”

34:53.310 --> 34:55.519
...was the pinnacle of my career,

34:56.185 --> 34:59.018
but in 2023 the Defense Ministry
had a change in strategy

34:59.019 --> 35:00.936
causing our production line to close.

35:01.602 --> 35:04.978
Namsun Paper merged with Mori Paper,

35:05.394 --> 35:09.018
and all specialty paper personnel
such as myself

35:09.019 --> 35:11.269
had to leave the company.

35:12.103 --> 35:16.185
I've now been 8 months between jobs,

35:16.644 --> 35:19.436
and I feel my batteries
are completely charged.

35:20.436 --> 35:22.060
During my extensive free time,

35:22.061 --> 35:23.310
I...

36:06.602 --> 36:07.936
Pulp Man of the Year

36:08.185 --> 36:09.394
Fire Safety Certification

36:31.853 --> 36:34.352
Worked 2 years at Ishii Paper in Japan

37:07.769 --> 37:08.393
North Korea Type 64 Pistol

37:08.394 --> 37:09.477
One,

37:11.728 --> 37:12.811
two,

37:14.978 --> 37:16.144
three men...

39:11.394 --> 39:12.853
How was your day?

39:17.519 --> 39:19.018
Daddy's day was hard.

39:20.519 --> 39:23.352
There's this house with
a beautiful pear tree,

39:24.561 --> 39:26.727
but bugs are eating it alive.

39:28.561 --> 39:30.144
It made me sad.

39:35.644 --> 39:40.728
In these circumstances,
we can't afford to feed so many mouths.

39:58.394 --> 39:59.977
Oh, fuck!

40:28.018 --> 40:30.102
Eating any old mushroom again!

40:30.436 --> 40:33.018
You quit drinking,
and now you'll eat anything?

40:35.310 --> 40:37.269
My back will ache without a blanket.

40:39.728 --> 40:40.977
Why would you lie down?

40:42.269 --> 40:43.436
Not scared of a snake?

40:52.728 --> 40:55.185
They haven't called for an interview.

40:55.477 --> 40:56.728
They'll call.

40:57.310 --> 40:58.769
Do like me.

40:59.893 --> 41:01.017
What?

41:01.018 --> 41:04.394
Wrap the sunlight in wind
and take a bite.

41:04.686 --> 41:07.394
With a dollop of foliage.

41:09.561 --> 41:12.519
I've always at least gotten an interview.

41:15.102 --> 41:16.185
What about me?

41:19.018 --> 41:21.310
I failed my audition again!

41:22.893 --> 41:25.309
My skin's too firm

41:25.310 --> 41:28.144
to play a woman wailing
over her husband's death.

41:31.144 --> 41:34.728
Still, it was nice being at
the Arts Center after so long.

41:39.060 --> 41:40.810
Remember the night of the blackout?

41:41.352 --> 41:42.768
Our first play seen together.

41:43.310 --> 41:45.268
In Act 2, suddenly the lights go out.

41:45.269 --> 41:48.768
People panic, women scream,

41:50.144 --> 41:52.351
and I was about to have a panic attack,

41:52.352 --> 41:53.851
when you appeared.

41:53.852 --> 41:55.685
Suddenly, from who knows where,

41:55.686 --> 41:57.726
like a streetlight turning on,

41:57.727 --> 41:58.977
your face...

42:01.269 --> 42:06.269
Please light a flame

42:08.686 --> 42:12.727
in my lonely heart...

42:13.060 --> 42:14.269
Smiling,

42:15.060 --> 42:16.602
you lead me to the door.

42:16.935 --> 42:20.018
“Ara, follow me. Only me.”

42:21.893 --> 42:23.018
“Watch your step.”

42:26.018 --> 42:27.102
“Are you okay?”

42:28.227 --> 42:30.977
I was at my most innocent then.

42:32.893 --> 42:34.644
Plump and pretty.

42:35.436 --> 42:37.727
I let you have my first kiss.

42:44.144 --> 42:45.810
Remember what you said?

42:49.310 --> 42:53.602
“Ara, your lips are softer than
the highest quality Okamoto

42:54.810 --> 42:55.852
tracing paper.”

42:56.852 --> 42:58.518
Akimoto.

42:58.519 --> 43:00.185
Okamoto is a condom brand.

43:01.394 --> 43:02.934
“Ara, your lips

43:02.935 --> 43:06.310
are softer than the highest quality
Akimoto tracing paper.”

43:15.810 --> 43:18.519
No message, no email.

43:18.768 --> 43:20.685
Paper, paper! Damned paper!

43:21.269 --> 43:24.059
My dad kept offering to
set you up with a café,

43:24.060 --> 43:25.852
but no, it had to be paper!

43:26.394 --> 43:30.643
Even if they hire you,
you'll retire in 6-7 years. What then?

43:31.060 --> 43:32.726
In an age of living to 100?

43:32.727 --> 43:35.017
You with your nice audio system,

43:35.018 --> 43:37.185
you could earn even more
with a music café!

43:37.602 --> 43:39.060
Know how I feel lately?

43:39.977 --> 43:43.519
I want to run through the mountains,
wailing like a madwoman!

43:45.185 --> 43:48.601
I'm like one of your precious
paper machines.

43:48.601 --> 43:50.435
Neglect me, and I'll break!

43:50.436 --> 43:53.852
Hurry up and smother me in that lube oil!

43:54.519 --> 43:58.477
Or I'll rip you to pieces.
Like tracing paper!

43:59.810 --> 44:01.935
Paper has fed me for 25 years.

44:03.102 --> 44:04.060
Honey.

44:05.018 --> 44:07.643
It's how I'm meant to be,
I've no other choice.

44:07.977 --> 44:10.852
You've been fed by the money
I earned from paper, too.

44:11.768 --> 44:13.810
That money was printed on paper I made,

44:14.185 --> 44:16.810
and the cigarette filter
you smoke is paper, too.

44:18.685 --> 44:20.934
If we don't use paper, who will?

44:20.935 --> 44:21.643
What?

44:23.768 --> 44:25.601
They won't send a text or email.

44:26.269 --> 44:27.767
The mailbox! The mailbox!

44:27.768 --> 44:28.394
Hey!

44:28.852 --> 44:29.519
Hey!

44:31.227 --> 44:33.269
I'm through with you!

44:33.685 --> 44:34.519
You...

44:35.519 --> 44:37.977
As useless as scrap paper!

44:40.102 --> 44:41.643
Sorry to keep you waiting.

44:43.144 --> 44:47.477
- I'll check before the doctor comes.
- Yes.

44:49.436 --> 44:50.768
You're a nurse?

44:51.560 --> 44:54.310
Dental hygienist. It's different.

44:56.726 --> 44:58.976
Don't you have dance class now?

44:58.977 --> 45:01.102
My tooth hurts too much.

45:02.436 --> 45:04.269
Then say “ah”.

45:07.144 --> 45:09.352
You'll come to the dance party, though?

45:10.227 --> 45:12.684
How can I? I quit the lessons.

45:12.685 --> 45:15.892
You can still come! Ask the teacher.

45:15.893 --> 45:17.809
Ms. Lee, go on home.

45:17.810 --> 45:19.476
You need to pick up Ri-one.

45:19.477 --> 45:20.310
Yes.

45:21.436 --> 45:25.725
You were a thing pure,
noble, honest, without stain!

45:25.726 --> 45:27.600
And now – oh!

45:27.601 --> 45:31.059
When I think that I made
of a man like you my ideal!

45:31.060 --> 45:33.810
Dear me! The ideal of my life!

45:37.144 --> 45:38.477
Fucking snake!

45:42.185 --> 45:43.935
Was its head triangle-shaped?

45:44.893 --> 45:47.518
Then it's a cannibal viper.
It'll eat its own mother.

45:48.685 --> 45:50.934
Or was it a black-and-white pattern?

45:50.935 --> 45:54.309
Then it's a 7-step mamushi.
You'll die before taking 7 steps.

45:54.310 --> 45:56.185
I think I heard a rattle, too.

45:57.518 --> 46:00.185
Keep the bite wound
higher than your heart.

46:04.269 --> 46:05.768
Shouldn't it be lower?

46:06.810 --> 46:10.352
Don't worry. I did this in a play once.

46:10.601 --> 46:11.601
Did what?

46:38.935 --> 46:40.601
- Honey, know what?
- Listen...

46:41.060 --> 46:42.517
A snake just bit me.

46:42.518 --> 46:44.768
- What?
- Might be poisonous, I'll call you back.

47:00.018 --> 47:02.810
Chase the snakes away like this.

47:03.727 --> 47:04.726
Damn it!

47:05.310 --> 47:08.685
1. Keep bite lower than heart.
2. Don't cut, or suck out poison.

47:10.643 --> 47:11.727
For god's sake!

47:12.685 --> 47:14.394
Shouldn't you go to the hospital?

47:14.935 --> 47:15.810
It's okay.

47:16.560 --> 47:18.935
If it were poisonous, I'd be dead now.

47:29.352 --> 47:30.435
What's with you?

47:34.018 --> 47:35.977
About the dance party...

47:36.393 --> 47:40.475
We better not go, right?
We quit the lessons.

47:40.476 --> 47:43.269
What? But we practiced so much.

47:46.935 --> 47:49.184
It's from the first mixtape you gave me.

47:49.185 --> 47:52.518
For a guy who only listens to '80s rock.

47:53.018 --> 47:54.810
I was blinded by love.

47:55.476 --> 47:58.018
I think I was prettiest back then.

47:58.351 --> 48:00.809
Even if I was a divorcee with a kid.

48:00.810 --> 48:02.810
Hey, don't talk like that.

48:03.144 --> 48:05.852
Of course, I earned more money than you.

48:07.060 --> 48:08.018
What?

48:08.351 --> 48:11.060
You think I proposed
because of your paycheck?

48:11.393 --> 48:14.060
Who knows? I had a college degree too.

48:15.269 --> 48:17.310
- So did I.
- Not back then.

48:19.601 --> 48:21.601
You're so mean. Forget it.

48:22.185 --> 48:25.809
You were busy doing
the distance degree while working.

48:25.810 --> 48:28.184
I wanted so much
to have fun with you then.

48:28.185 --> 48:31.517
Apologize, will you? Right now.

48:31.518 --> 48:32.560
You're right.

48:33.102 --> 48:38.102
Let's have 10 times more fun now
instead of wasting time complaining.

48:39.310 --> 48:41.227
When should we tell Si-one?

48:42.227 --> 48:43.476
Tell him what?

48:44.060 --> 48:47.144
We agreed to tell him
when he's old enough to shave.

48:48.518 --> 48:50.560
But do we have to tell him?

48:51.560 --> 48:54.102
I've been his dad since he was 2,
so I'm his dad.

48:59.727 --> 49:01.102
I'm sorry, Miri.

49:02.060 --> 49:05.727
You must want some lube oil too.
I've been so—

49:07.018 --> 49:08.560
Lube oil?

49:10.185 --> 49:11.476
It's not that.

49:12.601 --> 49:16.393
I've just been so busy these days
with job interviews.

49:17.102 --> 49:19.060
Does it have to be paper?

49:19.560 --> 49:21.227
How about some other job?

49:22.518 --> 49:23.601
What?

49:24.268 --> 49:25.351
Like a café?

49:26.560 --> 49:27.935
Why a café?

49:29.060 --> 49:31.768
Paper has fed me for 25 years, honey.

49:32.560 --> 49:34.601
It's how I'm meant to be.

49:35.518 --> 49:36.518
Think about it,

49:36.935 --> 49:40.476
would you tell a cannibal viper to
live off pear leaves?

49:40.852 --> 49:43.393
It's meant to eat its mother.

49:46.893 --> 49:50.102
- Is that so, Mr. You?
- Yes.

49:50.309 --> 49:52.060
- Mr. You.
- Yes?

49:52.435 --> 49:53.768
You're not a bad dancer.

49:54.685 --> 49:56.268
Follow me. Only me.

49:57.476 --> 50:00.018
Guess you overdid the vibrato.

50:16.102 --> 50:18.393
This will be the best job interview ever.

50:18.726 --> 50:20.185
Slay them all!

50:20.810 --> 50:23.185
Okay, I'll slay them all.

50:23.351 --> 50:24.768
Green light!

50:57.893 --> 50:59.060
Chun-oh!

50:59.935 --> 51:01.184
Chun-oh!

51:07.435 --> 51:12.267
Doing it on your bed is great, ma'am.
It doesn't even creak.

51:12.268 --> 51:14.892
Don't call me ma'am!

51:14.893 --> 51:18.060
Tell your husband not to quit

51:19.018 --> 51:22.102
that group for quitting drinking.
This is great.

52:00.977 --> 52:02.226
Minsan City...

52:22.309 --> 52:25.434
Hello, this is Red Pepper Paper.

52:25.435 --> 52:26.727
Oh, hello!

52:27.351 --> 52:29.183
- Hey, don't!
- What?

52:29.184 --> 52:31.393
Yes? Hello? What was that?

52:31.977 --> 52:33.393
I'm having trouble hearing you.

52:34.268 --> 52:35.559
I can hear you fine.

52:35.560 --> 52:38.143
I heard well from the spot
where you first answered.

52:39.018 --> 52:42.268
I see! I'm heading there now.

52:42.435 --> 52:43.268
Stop!

52:43.518 --> 52:45.018
That spot is perfect.

52:46.060 --> 52:47.725
You can hear best from here?

52:47.726 --> 52:49.685
Yes, I can hear you great now.

52:50.476 --> 52:53.852
By any chance are you
at your home in Minsan City?

52:54.726 --> 52:55.600
I am.

52:55.601 --> 52:57.685
My boss would like to meet you.

52:58.476 --> 53:01.101
He's very curious about you, Mr. Gu.

53:01.768 --> 53:03.142
- However...
- Yes?

53:03.143 --> 53:07.935
My boss is returning to Zurich
on a 5pm flight.

53:08.977 --> 53:14.101
I'm sorry, but if you leave from Minsan
right now, you should have time.

53:15.685 --> 53:16.726
Right now?

53:17.018 --> 53:18.977
Guess it's too much to ask?

53:20.018 --> 53:23.600
